post_text:
On the morning of September 11 2001, 2,976 people from 93 nations lost their lives in New York, at the Pentagon, and on Flight 93.
Today, we pause to remember that moment of horror and pray for those left scarred by those terrible events.

We remember the first time we
heard the news.
We recall the first time we saw those images.
We remember the way our thoughts
and prayers were with those families
who lost loved ones.
Our thoughts and prayers are with them again today.

post_text: Just a reminder to parents that students will not have homework (for now). The devices & chargers at home are for "just in case" we have to go virtual at the last minute. If students forget devices at home & someone is not able to bring it to them, they will not be given another device & then will have to complete the day's assignments at home. Student devices will not work after 7pm during the week and will not work on the weekends. If extenuating circumstances arise, we can make accommodations, but for now, these are the parameters. Please let Mrs. Schaffer know if you have any questions.

LAC School Community,
Thank you for your patience, cooperation, & flexibility during these uncertain times. We have been working extremely hard to develop a plan to allow a safe & successful return to school for our students & staff for the 20-21 school year.

Good morning! We know this is last minute, however, we just received notice that we will be getting a produce delivery today. We will have 150 FREE produce kits available from 11am-2pm to any LAC resident. You DO NOT have to sign up. They will be first come, first served.

Pick up will be at the cafeteria door in the back of the school.

Kits include: 3lbs of apples, 4lbs oranges, 1lb carrots, 1 head of celery, 3 cucumbers, 1 pint grape tomatoes, 2 onions, 6 potatoes, and a 3 pack of romaine hearts!

post_text:
12 Months

January brings snow, makes your freeze.
February brings rain, makes the lake unfreeze.
March brings the breeze, that makes you dance
April brings may flowers, daisies at your feet
May brings pretty lambs, lambs running thru the grass
June brings rose, fills kids hands with joy
July brings cooled showers
August brings my birthday at the end
September brings fruit, makes good sportsmanship
October brings you haunted feeling
November brings pumpkins
December brings a sheet of ice, makes Christmas treats

By: Julianna (6th grade)

post_text: Hi LAC Family! Ms. Laws wants you to know that many students have books checked out of the library. We want to get as many back as possible. Please go to lacschool.follettdestiny.com & log in to your child's account to see what books they have checked out. Each username is the last name, first initial, last two digits of grad year. For example 8th grader John Smith would be smithj20. The passwords are the grad year. So John Smith would use password 2020. Books can be returned when you come in to drop off/pick up school items. Please email me if you have any questions- slaws@lacschool.org

Week 9 day 3

Cardio and lower body

1- lap around your house
12- lunges
10- squat jumps
20- mountain climbers

X3

Hey guys thinking ahead, next week what I’d like to do is have you guys create a workout similar to what we have been doing for the last 9 weeks and submit it to me and I’ll pick five workouts and film them and post them to the LAC Facebook page. We will all do these workouts as a school. It’s your turn to be the teacher and I am the student. Feel free to dress up in your best Mr.Cullen attire and your best Mr.Cullen impersonation... let’s have fun with it !! So feel free to start putting together ideas, workouts, and attire and be the best PE teacher you can be.

Core muscle training

30 second plank
Center, left, right
15 crunches

X3

In the video I talk about some technical points to keep in mind as you’re going through the workout.

Also take breaks as needed. If you need to break up the 30 seconds go ahead and do that. Another great thing about body weight exercises Is that you can always modify the movement for all ability levels.

Week 8 day 4

Test day

2 minutes max Burpees

Hips and chest must touch the floor each rep.

At the top hands must come above shoulders, feet must leave the floors.

Pace yourself and try your best to stay moving for the entire 2 minutes... doesn’t sound like a lot of time but during full body exercise it’s a long time.

Monday test !!! Whatttttt ???

3 min jog to warm up the body

Than set you cameras and stop watch for 2 minutes and perform as many air squats as possible in 2 minutes.

This is a great way to build lower body endurance and strength.

Sit your bottoms back and down and stand all the way up for each repetition.

Let’s video and see how many we can do in two minutes.

Dear LAC Parents/Guardians,

We are very happy to announce that effective immediately, the NJ Department of Agriculture is allowing the Lower Alloways Creek School District to provide meals FREE of charge to ALL students enrolled in the LAC School, regardless of eligibility status.

Please contact Susan Schaffer, CSA, at sschaffer@lacschool.org if you would like the school to provide your student breakfast & lunch free of charge or if you have any questions.

5th Grade Winner--Laura C.
4th Grade Winner--Lux H.
3rd Grade Winner--Emma S.

Congratulations!! I'm so proud of you!

post_text:
Hey guys sorry a little bit late today !!
This workout came from Mrs. Christine!!
Each letter of your name is a different exercise. Spell out your FULL name [first and last]and see what exercises you get to perform.

M- 30 leg lifts ( lay on your back and alternate lifting your legs towards the ceiling).
I- 10 Jump squats
C- 30 squats
H-20 lunges
A- 25 jumping jacks
E- 1 minute walk sit( sit against the wall with your back flat and knees bend to 90 degrees)
L- 30 second wall sit lol that was fun

C- 30 squats
U- 20 bicycle kicks ( lay on your back and alternate your knees towards your chest)
L- 30 second wall sit
L- 30 second wall sit
E- 60 second wall sit... legs are burning lol feeling strong 💪🏼
N- 40 jumping jacks

For a bonus if you want more work add your middle name to the workout.
